Food is excellent. You can have it fried, steamed or broiled. Wait time is long but at least you know it's fresh. Still not sure why any business today won't take cards instead of cash only.

I have been to this place for years and it's a gem. The food is fresh and cannot get enough of The Fish, Shrimp, and Chips. The owners make you feel at home. It is simple, not fancy. Waiting in Line for your order after Rush Hour is worth it! Looking for good old fashioned cooking? This is the place for you.
Unbelievable. Well worth the wait.

I had the fish and chips, and the fried calamari. Both were very tasty. If you're looking for fried fish etc. this place is great. The fries are cooked very well too.  That being said, it's still pretty salty, extremely fatty, and the flavors sort of don't go too much further than that. I understand that's generally what fried fish and chips is like, and is why I still give it 4 stars.

The best things in life require the exercise of patience. Never disappointed...always hot, always good. If you know what you want call ahead. My favs...broiled salmon, garlic broccoli, spanish rice and sweet plantain.
